was based upon, and followed the early Aryan calculations -- to realize
the immense periods of time that must have elapsed since the separation
of the sexes, without mentioning the First or even the Second
Root-Races. As these must remain beyond the comprehension of minds
trained in Western thought, it is found useless to speak in detail of
the First and Second, and even of the Third Race in its earliest
stage.\* One has to begin with the latter, when it reached its full
human period, lest the uninitiated reader should find himself hopelessly
