In the Kabalistic books, and in the *Zohar* pre-eminently, the idea that
everything objective on earth or in this Universe is the Shadow --
*Dyooknah* -- of the eternal Light or Deity, is very strong.

The Third Race was pre-eminently the bright shadow, at first, of the
gods, whom tradition exiles on Earth after the allegorical war in
Heaven; which became still more allegorical on Earth, for it was the war
between spirit and matter. This war will last till the inner and divine
man adjusts his outer terrestrial self to his own spiritual nature. Till
then the dark and fierce passions of the former will be at eternal feud
with his master, the Divine Man. But the *animal* will be tamed one day,
because its nature will be changed, and harmony will reign once more
between the two as before the "Fall," when even mortal man was *created*
by the Elements and was not born.

